Peru Stocks: Atacocha, Candente, Ferreyros, Southern, Telefonica

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-06-30T20:43:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-30/peru-stocks-atacocha-candente-ferreyros-southern-telefonica.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:10 p.m.  New York  time.  The Lima General Index rose for the first session in eight,
recovering 0.9 percent to 18,878.78. The MSCI All Peru Capped
Index rose 0.3 percent to 2,463.21.  Utilities, industrial and banking stocks gained after
yesterday’s Peruvian holiday as U.S. stocks rallied, said
Sebastian Blondet, a trader at Celfin Capital SAB.  Telefonica del Peru SAA (TEF PE), the local unit of
 Telefonica SA (TEF) , rose 5.2 percent to $24. Austral Group SA
(AUSTRAC1 PE), a unit of Austevoll Seafood ASA, advanced 3.6
percent to 29 centimos.  Ferreyros SA (FERREYC1)  (FERREYC1 PE), the Lima-
based distributor for Caterpillar Inc., gained 3.2 percent to
2.62 soles.  Scotiabank Peru SA (SCOTIAC1)  (SCOTIAC1 PE), the local unit of
 Canada ’s third-largest bank, rose 2.8 percent to 45.05 soles.  Copper, zinc and silver miners rebounded as the metals
advanced in New York and  London .  Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian exploration
company, jumped 6.3 percent to $1.19 after awarding geotechnical
design of its Canariaco mine to Knight Piesold Ltd.  Southern
Copper Corp. (SCCO)  , Peru’s biggest copper producer, rose 4.3
percent to $33.05. Cia. Minera Atacocha SA (ATACOBC1 PE), the
Lima-based silver and zinc mining company, gained 2.9 percent to
1.07 soles. Cia. de Minas Buenaventura SAA (BVN PE), the
country’s biggest precious-metals miner, rose 1.5 percent to
$37.80.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in  Lima  at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  